This incident could once again raise questions about the safety of materials used on the exterior of high-rise buildings worldwide.
In an investigation carried out by the Torch Board after the 2015 fire, it was found that the most damage was suffered by the facade covering - decorative panels and insulation of the exterior surface.
Police in the United Kingdom say they believe that the insulation of London's Grenfell Tower and the facade panels may have contributed to the rapid spread of the fire in June, which killed some 80 people.
