"For some metals, it changes everything," said Simona Gambranini, a commodity analyst at Capital Economics, to Bloomberg.
We have already seen a great impact on metals such as cobalt and lithium, the demand for which has been increasing for years.
Electric cars have about three times more copper than a conventional car, Glencore reported.
