Glencore's stock rose 20 percent in London, having exceeded rivals Rio Tinto Group, BHP Billiton and Anglo American from price rises.
On the losing side are lead companies like Recyclex and Campine, who need to adapt to the new era.
The main end-use of lead is the power-supplying battery of petrol and diesel car starters.
Electric cars use lithium-ion batteries.
"This is a serious risk to lead demand unless another purpose is found to it, which could overcome a drop in demand," said Michael Widmer, head of metals analysis at Bank of America Merrill Lynch.
