The Spanish league, clearly upset about the departure of one of the biggest football stars, tried to stop Neymar from the transfer, arguing that PSG was violating the FFP.
"This is a clear case of 'financial doping' with the club and the state," La Liga president Javier Tebas told Spanish newspaper AS, pointing out that PSG belonged mainly to Qatar.
