From the Philippines to the wide world, or the straw bag trip to the hearts of fashion fans
Straw-braided bags are a summer classic that has become a hit product in its own right in recent years, which has to hang on the end of a real summer enthusiast and to which merchants have been able to weld an additional price tag suitable for the hit, despite its modest origin.
A straw-braided bag is probably one of those things that has ever existed once in a lifetime and that has not caused any special emotions.
It just exists, and if it doesn't, there's nothing broken.
Now, however, straw bags are making a real triumph, and fashion fans have exchanged their fine designer bags for the summer months for simple straw-braided bags.
At the same time, it is not only a beach bag, but today it is just as popular as a street bag, and braver women even walk to the office with it.
At this point, however, it is worth making it clear whether the boss is still sitting on such a summer look or whether it is still worth pushing the notebook and laptop to a slightly more official sumada.
However, variety has made straw bags a true summer love of women.
For example, when reading foreign fashion blogs, the first thing that catches your eye is that fashion gourmets rush to the local market first on a holiday trip and buy themselves a straw bag, to which they are faithful throughout their vacation and which goes with them on the beach, in the market and also when hanging out with their girlfriends on the city.
Some bloggers are so generous that they buy a bigger pile of bags from the market and sell or give them away to their loyal readers.
At the same time, it is worth noting that the demand for bags is so great among readers that in the real world, women (and men!) would probably go to work with each other by hand to become the happy owner of some bags.
In a way, such madness is also understandable, because it is rare that in the fashion world it is possible to buy a thing that has risen to the status of a hit for only a few dozen euros.
True, clever merchants have also discovered a simple way to earn money here, and so finer luxury brands also sell straw bags for a few hundred and a thousand euros.
