For example, it is possible to buy a straw bag that costs more than a thousand euros in Dolce & Gabbana.
However, the interpretation of the Chanel straw bag can be spent around 6000 euros.
Unlike most fashion hits, however, straw bags do not come from some great fashion mecca, but their story started much further away.
The straw bags are said to have originated in the far Philippines, where they have been carried around.
Braiding a bag from straw is primarily an export business there, and you don't see the locals walking around with them very often.
The straw weaving technique is said to have dated back to the 14th century and is quite similar to ordinary basket weaving.
However, since the straw bag does not have to be weaved as tightly as the basket, patterns and other materials can be embedded in them, which make the bag more personal and thus more attractive.
For example, there have been trendy bags with colored ribbons or leather strips that have been braided in.
