For example, if you wish, you can buy a straw-braided cloth or a tiny shoulder bag.
At the same time, it is worth remembering that a classic straw bag never goes out of fashion, but the straw bag does.
But what is a classic straw bag?
For centuries, a straw-braided bag that resembles a basket in style, is open on top and has short, as well as straw, handles.
Five healthy ice creams that are easy to make at home
Lifehack.org highlighted ways to make different types of ice creams at home that contain fewer calories than store ice creams.
Lemon and buttermilk ice cream - whisk in a large bowl of lemon juice with the sugar, add the buttermilk and whipped cream and mix everything into an even mass, place the mixture in the refrigerator.
Chocolate and nut butter ice cream - blend Greek yogurt, frozen bananas, cocoa powder and maple syrup until smooth.
Then add a little peanut butter to the mixture and blend the mixture for a few seconds.
The ice cream is ready to eat immediately.
Peach ice cream - in a bowl, mix the fat-free milk, sugar substitute, egg, frozen or ordinary peach slices and almond extract into a smooth mass and place the resulting mixture in the refrigerator to harden.
Coconut ice cream - blend coconut milk, coconut flakes, vanilla extract, maple syrup and frozen bananas and place the resulting mixture in the refrigerator.
Banana ice cream - in a bowl, mix the frozen banana pieces with low-fat milk until smooth, serve with walnuts and consume immediately.
